Cases in various countries
Americas
---
[Map showing the location of affected areas in South America can be seen at https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=6638589,6186. - Mod.TY]

South America
---
Brazil
- National. 18 Aug 2019. (Probable [prob]) 97 900 cases, up from 72 000 for the same period last year (2018).
http://outbreaknewstoday.com/chikungunya-brazil-reports-nearly-100k-cases-through-july-94515/

- Santa Catarina state. 16 Aug 2019. As of 10 Aug 2019 (Confirmed [conf]) 28 cases, all imported from states: Rio de Janeiro, Rio Grande do Norte, Para, Sao Paulo, Alagoas, Mato Grosso and Maranhao.
https://www.nsctotal.com.br/noticias/santa-catarina-confirma-62-casos-de-dengue-em-14-dias [in Portuguese]

Africa
---
Ethiopia (Dire Dawa city). 13 Aug 2019. (Reported [rep]) 3756 cases.
https://www.politicalanalysis.co.za/dire-dawa-reports-over-3-000-cases-connected-to-the-chikungunya-outbreak/

[HealthMap/ProMED map of Ethiopia: https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=6638589,95]

Asia
---
Taiwan. 4 Aug 2019. (conf) one locally acquired case, 24 imported cases from Myanmar (12 cases), the Maldives, Thailand and India.
http://focustaiwan.tw/news/asoc/201908040007.aspx

[HealthMap/ProMED-mail map of Taiwan: https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=6638589,193]

Thailand. 21 Aug 2019. As of 14 Aug 2019 (rep) 6289 cases in 45 provinces; incidence: 9.52 persons per 100 000 population, the highest in 5 years. Localities most affected: 4988 in the South, 1008 in the North, 143 in the Central region and 78 in the Northeast. The southern provinces of Tak, Pattani, Phitsanulok, Surat Thani, and Songkhla were the worst hit.
https://www.thestar.com.my/news/regional/2019/08/21/chikungunya-virus-has-mutated-offering-greater-risk-warns-doctor

[Thailand maps: http://legacy.lib.utexas.edu/maps/middle_east_and_asia/thailand_trans-2013.jpg and https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=6638589,53814]

